  schema:name "How to Map the Feedback Layers of a Platform" ;
  schema:description "A working procedure for analyzing a platform as a Viable System Model implementation: identify principal users, map the four nested feedback layers (real-time operations, campaign cycles, product development, identity scanning) and their connections, apply Ashby's requisite variety, and identify what the architecture admits and refuses." ;
